com.camerontec.catalys.fixtesttool.utils

Class FIXFieldUtils

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.camerontec.catalys.fixtesttool.utils.FIXFieldUtils

  • public final class FIXFieldUtils
extends Object
    FIX field information utility class.

    In order to implement some methods a specific FIX dictionary must be specified. However, this unnecessarily limits the usefulness of this class by enforcing strictness not really applicable to a testing tool. In these cases a number of dictionaries are used to try to fulfil the request.

      • toFIXTagAsInt

        public int toFIXTagAsInt(String tagNumberOrName)
        Convert the specified tag number or name into its FIX integer equivalent.

        If the specified tagNumberOrName can be parsed as an integer it is, otherwise it is assumed to be a FIX tag name in the current FIX dictionary.

        Parameters:
        tagNumberOrName - The FIX tag number or name represented as a string.
        Returns:
        The integer FIX tag associated with the specified tagNumberOrName.

        Returns:

      • toFIXValueAsString

        public String toFIXValueAsString(int tag,
                                 String valueName)
        Attempt to convert the specified value name for the specified tag to its equivalent FIX value.
        Parameters:
        tag - The FIX tag.
        valueName - The FIX value name.
        Returns:
        The equivalent FIX field value if the specified value name is recognized as a valid value for the specified tag, or the specified value name is not recognized.

      • getNumberInGroupTag

        public int getNumberInGroupTag(String msgType,
                               int repeatingGroupTag)
        Return the number in group tag associated with the specific repeating group tag and message.
        Parameters:
        msgType - The message type.
        repeatingGroupTag - The repeating group tag.
        Returns:
